After you create a cloud account, you can set limits on the resources that belong to each logical datacenter (LDC) in the cloud account. Setting these limits is especially important for capacity constrained environments like private clouds. 
 
Assign capacity limits for the following resource types: 
  • Virtual Servers
  • vCPUs
  • Storage Volume Size
  • Network 
You can also set per-user and total capacity limitations on resources by using quotas. See the Assign Quotas section of Guided Setup.

  • Open a cloud account and click the Capacity Limits tab. The capacity attributes appear along with the current values for each.
  • Set the capacity limits for virtual machines, virtual CPUs, virtual networks, and storage volume size. These are supported by default.
  • Click Update
